 Creating an Android Application that uses OpenCV and native C++ code

  - make sure java JDK is installed
  - download Android SDK (android-sdk-linux) and extract somewhere (anywhere)
  - add to $PATH : android-sdk-linux/tools
		   android-sdk-linux/platform-tools
  - create a project folder for the app and use the command 'android' to create the skeleton:
       android create project --target android-17 --name SomeAppName --path path/to/project/folder --activity SomeName --package de.visus.some.namespace
  - ... more to come    

